# /etc/network/interfaces.d/00-netfirewall-bootstrap
#
# First-boot reachability ONLY. NIC names are unknown at image-build time, so we
# can't hardcode eth0/ens256. This file is installed by the ISO into the image
# and brings up loopback + DHCP on the first physical NIC found, so a freshly
# flashed appliance is reachable on the network and the operator can open the
# web UI.
#
# Once the operator runs the SetupWizard, the daemon (via
# DebianInterfacesConfigService) writes the REAL per-NIC config into other files
# under /etc/network/interfaces.d/ and this bootstrap file is superseded /
# removed. Do NOT treat this as the production interface config.
#
# NOTE: the actual NIC name is substituted at first boot by
# netfirewall-issue-banner / a tiny generator that reads /sys/class/net — this
# file ships with the literal token __FIRST_NIC__ which the firstboot network
# hook replaces. If left as-is, ifupdown ignores the unknown stanza harmlessly.

auto lo
iface lo inet loopback

allow-hotplug __FIRST_NIC__
iface __FIRST_NIC__ inet dhcp
